Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @sweet potato{2} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide chips (no need to peel). Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt and @ground black pepper then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. 

> Use two baking trays if necessary. 

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Put the garlic, @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}, @chermoula spice mix{1%packet} and @water{2%tbsp} into a large #bowl{}, then mix to combine. Add the @lamb mince{300%g}, season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and @ground black pepper, then mix together with your hands. Roll the mince into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers (1 per person).

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto a lightly oiled baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim and halve the @cucumber{1/2} lengthways. Scoop out the seeds and discard, then coarsely grate half of it. Place the grated cucumber in a #sieve{} and press with the back of a #spoon{} to remove as much water as possible then pop into a small bowl along with the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}. Season with @salt and @ground black pepper, then mix well.

Chop the remaining cucumber into small pieces. Crumble the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g}. In another bowl, mix together the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing, then season with @salt and @ground black pepper. Chop the @medium tomato{2}(chopped into 2cm pieces) and toss in the dressing. Just before serving, add the chopped cucumber and @olives{30} to the bowl with the tomatoes and mix together. Halve the @glazed burger bun{2} and pop onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything is ready, spread the tzatziki onto the base of each bun. Lay the burgers on top, then close with the bun lids. Serve the lamb burgers on your plates with the sweet potato chips and salad alongside. Scatter the Greek style salad cheese over the salad to finish. Enjoy!